File: Unilever has accepted the ad campaign was racist and offensive and agreed to pull TRESemmé products off shelves for 10 days. JOHANNESBURG - Tensions between the EFF and Unilever may be over. The parties reached an agreement earlier on Thursday. READ: Woolies, Dis-Chem pull TRESemmé products off shelves Unilever has accepted the ad campaign was racist and offensive. It's agreed to pull TRESemmé products off shelves for 10 days. READ: TRESemmé apologises for Clicks ad It will also donate 10,000 sanitary towels and sanitiser to informal settlements identified by the EFF. The company is, however, refusing to publish the names of those responsible. The EFF says it now considers the matter closed.